        checkConfigIntervalMs - Interval between checks for new configuration

      • setConfigurationManager

        public void setConfigurationManager(RssConfigurationManager configurationManager)
        The configuration manager extends RssConfigurationManager and specifies which RssSites are used. The default, if no other is specified, is the CxmlConfigurationManager. This method may not be invoked after the controller is started. The configuration manager may not be null.
        Parameters:
        configurationManager - The configuration manager to use. Can not be null.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If invoked after starting controller
        NullPointerException - If passed a null value

        public void setCrawlLogToPreloadUriUniqFilter(String log)
        Set this value to a fully qualified path pointing at an existing crawl log if you want the uriUniqFilter to be preloaded with all URLs in the crawl log.
        Parameters:
        log - The fully qualified path of a crawl log file

      • aboutToSchedule

        public void aboutToSchedule(org.archive.modules.CrawlURI curi)
        Inform that a CURI is up for scheduling.

        Mostly this is for notification, but it may also be ruled out-of-scope if the same non-derived link has been found in the current feed update.

        Parameters:
        curi - The CrawlURI
